Bring a large pot of water to a boil, season with salt. Combine spinach, parsley, garlic, cheese (optional) and 6 tablespoons of olive oil in a food processor. Process until smooth to make pesto. Saute tomatoes with remaining olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat until blistered, add salt and pepper to taste. Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain pasta and toss it with pesto and tomatoes in a large mixing bowl before serving.